name: Walking
detail: Walking is one of the main gaits of terrestrial locomotion among legged animals. Walking is typically slower than running and other gaits.

name: Swimming
detail: Swimming is the self-propulsion of a person through water, or other liquid, usually for recreation, sport, exercise, or survival.

name: Running
detail: Running is a method of terrestrial locomotion allowing humans and other animals to move rapidly on foot.
